    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - MOUNTING ENGINE ON STAND - MOUNTING ENGINE ON STAND
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="10">
        <title>MOUNTING ENGINE ON STAND</title>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Perform the following steps before installing engine to mounting stand:</emph>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil pan drain plug and plug gasket. Drain all engine oil and discard gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall oil pan drain plug together with new plug gasket. Refer to Special Torque Value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using an open end wrench, loosen oil feed supply tube nut located on top of oil filter
                header. Remove and discard tube nut sleeve. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050101">1.1</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two (2) mounting bolts securing oil feed supply tube to top of turbocharger housing.
                Remove oil feed supply tube and tube flange gasket. Discard flange gasket. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050102">1.2</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050101" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1722" filename="../figeg1/EG1722.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.1.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Oil Filter Header</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Oil Feed Supply Tube Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Feed Supply Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050102" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1969" filename="../figeg1/EG1969.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.2.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Turbocharger Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Oil Feed Supply Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove turbocharger oil drain tube as follows: (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050103">1.3</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                )
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove one bolt securing turbocharger oil drain tube retaining plate to crankcase.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove two (2) capscrews securing turbocharger oil drain tube to bottom of turbocharger
                    housing.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove turbocharger oil drain tube retaining plate together with turbocharger oil drain
                    tube, tube flange, two tube O-Rings and tube flange gasket from bottom of turbocharger assembly.
                    Discard both drain tube O-Rings (one on each end of drain tube) and flange gasket.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050103" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1724" filename="../figeg1/EG1724.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.3.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube Flange Gasket</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Turbocharger Assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Oil Drain Tube Mounting Bolts (2)</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Turbocharger Oil Drain Tube Retaining Plate</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. Oil Drain Tube Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil filter from oil cooler filter header. Discard oil filter. (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050104">1.4</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .)
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove coolant filter from header. Discard old coolant filter. (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050105">1.5</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .)
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050104" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1970" filename="../figeg1/EG1970.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.4.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Oil Cooler Filter</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Oil Filter Header</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050105" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1971" filename="../figeg1/EG1971.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.5. Coolant Filter Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Coolant Filter</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Coolant Filter Header</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Remove oil cooler and water coolant supply tube as an assembly.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove one (1) bolt and retainer plate securing water coolant supply tube from crankcase.
                (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050106">1.6</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .)
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil cooler assembly as follows: (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050107">1.7</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .)
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove bolts securing oil cooler filter header and front header to crankcase.</para>
                <figure id="ef1050106" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1972" filename="../figeg1/EG1972.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.6.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Retainer Plate Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Retaining Plate</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Water Coolant Supply Tube</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050107" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg1973" filename="../figeg1/EG1973.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.7.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Mounting Bolt (2)</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Mounting Bolt (5 Long)</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Oil Cooler Filter Header</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Oil Cooler Bundle</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">. Remove oil cooler and water coolant supply tube as an assembly from crankcase. (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050108">1.8</hotlnk>.
                </emph>
                )
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">. Remove oil pressure regulating valve assembly from the crankcase. (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050108">1.8</hotlnk>.
                </emph>
                )
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>The oil pressure regulating valve should be tagged upon removal to ensure identification. DO
                        NOT mix oil pressure regulator valve with oil pressure relief valve (found in front cover).
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">. Cap
                <emph type="bold">ALL</emph>openings to prevent debris from entering.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>WHENEVER MOUNTING AN ENGINE TO A REPAIR STAND, REFER TO THE INSTRUCTIONS INCLUDED WITH THE
                        MOUNTING STAND AND ITS CORRESPONDING ADAPTER PLATES FOR SPECIFIC DIRECTIONS ON THEIR SAFE USE.
                        USE ONLY METRIC M-10/GRADE 8 BOLTS WHEN MOUNTING THE ENGINE TO AN ENGINE STAND.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">. Install recommended adapter plate
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE 4151A</emph>
                as directed. Refer to instructions included with engine stand and secure adapter plate to side of
                engine. (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050109">1.9</hotlnk>.
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Adapter plate must be mounted to engine first before installing engine stand. Locating guide
                        pins (made locally) are recommended to assist in aligning and holding adapter plate.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef1050108" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1974" filename="../figeg1/EG1974.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.8.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Oil Cooler Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Oil Pressure Regulating Valve</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Water Coolant Supply Tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1050109" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1728" filename="../figeg1/EG1728.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.9.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Hoist Hook</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Lifting Bar</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Lifting Eye (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Adapter Plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>CAUTION SHOULD BE USED WHEN HOISTING THE ENGINE TO THE STAND TO AVOID DAMAGE TO VALVE
                        COVER/INTAKE MANIFOLD. USE A SAFETY CATCH ON THE HOIST HOOK WHEN LIFTING THE ENGINE BY THE
                        LIFTING EYES.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">. Attach engine stand to adapter plate. (Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050110">1.10</hotlnk>.
                </emph>
                )
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1050110" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1731" filename="../figeg1/EG1731.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.10.</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Engine Stand</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. Adapter Plate</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
